# ESP32 CPU Frequency Test

This example demonstrates how to read and modify the **ESP32 CPU clock frequency** using Arduino functions. 
One program sets the CPU frequency to **10 MHz** using `setCpuFrequencyMhz()` and prints the CPU, XTAL, and APB frequencies.
The second program reads and prints the default system frequencies without changing them. A GPIO pin is toggled continuously to observe timing differences when the CPU frequency changes. 
This example helps understand **clock configuration and performance scaling in ESP32**.
